---
title: BLT Salad with Crispy Chickpeas plus Croutons & Creamy Red Wine Vinaigrette
description: This twist on a BLT is welcome on our table any time at all! Bacon does double duty here: as the star of the salad, and providing the flavorful fat in which you’ll roast chickpeas to crispy perfection. Fresh lettuce, juicy grape tomatoes, and crunchy croutons are tossed in a quick homemade Dijon-oregano vinaigrette that ties it all together.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/667ac73ee4ccb870eb4daedf-c8182762.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/667ac73ee4ccb870eb4daedf-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 52 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1420 mg
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/blt-salad-with-crispy-chickpeas-667ac73ee4ccb870eb4daedf
---

Heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce} and cook, turning
occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too fast, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer bacon to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Once cool enough
to handle, roughly chop. Carefully discard all but 1 TBSP bacon fat (2 TBSP for 4
servings) from pan (you'll use it to toast the chickpeas in Step 3).

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}; pat dry
with paper towels. Trim and discard root end of @baby lettuce{2%unit}; separate leaves
and cut into bite-size pieces. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}.

> Be sure chickpeas are thoroughly dried off to ensure even toasting!

Heat pan with reserved bacon fat over medium-high heat. (TIP: If your bacon
didn't yield enough fat, add a drizzle of oil to pan.) Once pan is hot, add
chickpeas and cook, covered, shaking the pan occasionally, until lightly
browned and crispy, ~{2-4%minutes}. (Chickpeas will pop. Be careful!) Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, whisk together @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon},
@mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, half the
@dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon},
a pinch of salt, and pepper (all the oregano, 2 TBSP olive oil, and 1 tsp sugar
for 4 servings).

Once chickpeas are done, add lettuce, tomatoes, toasted chickpeas, and
@croutons{1%unit}(crushed in the bag first) to bowl with vinaigrette. Toss
to coat.

Divide salad between #bowls{} and top with bacon. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.